Description:
Federation flavour, timeless appeal
From lofty ceilings to delicate details blended with a modern kitchen and relaxing outdoor spaces, this three bedroom period home exudes appeal in a corner position near Coburg Market. Complementing a central living room is a kitchen/meals filled with quality appliances, from names including Bosch and Electrolux, matched with dark stone countertops. A covered entertaining area awaits outside along with handy places to grow delicious fresh produce. Well proportioned bedrooms offer robes and the neat bathroom teams with a full laundry. Additional features include polished floorboards, high ceilings with rosettes, coloured glass, ducted heating and a reverse cycle air conditioner, plus there's OSP for two. Stroll to transport, playgrounds, True North cafe and buzzing Sydney Road.
Insights: 120 Munro Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2020 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Superb House, Top Spot!
In a neighbourly street close to picturesque Merri Creek Trail, you will love this 3 bedroom, updated, brick veneer home.
Upon entry be impressed by the tiled, open plan family room/kitchen with s/steel appliances including a 'chef's oven', dishwasher & ample bench space with island bench, all with 'Caesar stone' finish. Formal living room or potential for 4th bedroom. 3, extra-large bedrooms all with BIRs. Sparkling, modern bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles, additional powder room & separate laundry.
Remote, extra-large garage or potential for a kid's rumpus room with workshop & great under house storage.
Extra features include; ducted heating, evaporative cooling, two driveways with carport also. City tram 300m walk (approx.), station only 2km (approx.) away & fantastic schools nearby.
Plan your life here!

The Nicholson- Architecturally designed

It's light-filled interior boasts two double bedrooms (both with built-in robes), stone-benchtops with integrated dishwasher, double glazed windows allowing for perfect climate control, 6 star energy rating encompassing the environmentally aware precinct of the Merri Creek and an open living/dining area which leads out onto a balcony, just perfect for entertaining. Description:
Designer Living over two levels with Amazing Views
Designed by Splinter Society Architecture, this spacious light filled residence offers excellent low maintenance living over two levels with direct access into the CBD via train or tram. Highlights include two bedrooms with built in robes (first bedroom has a large storage walk in robe), central bathroom and separate laundry area. The master bedroom has direct access onto the outdoor balcony. The entrance to upstairs is welcomed by a wide staircase to an open plan dining, kitchen and living area looking out to a generous outdoor balcony with bi folding glass windows on both levels . Other features include loads of storage, heating and cooling throughout , polished hardwood timber floors , secure off street parking , stone bench tops, European cooking appliances, separate storage unit on the ground floor and secure intercom access into the property.

Description:
Modern and Luxurious Living at it's Finest
Without a shadow of a doubt, this is one of the best brand-new constructions on the market today.
Immediately impressive, the free-flowing floor plans begin with a grand entrance of which there is good-sized bedroom plus bathroom. This leads onto your expansive open plan living area boasting a sleek kitchen with stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, stone benches as well as plenty of natural light from your magnificent courtyard. Located in the heart of Coburg you're within a short stroll to Sydney Road shops, cafés and tram. You are also within walking distance to Coburg Train Station which makes access to the CBD a breeze.
If you are looking for a turnkey property in an A+ location, this is the one for you.

Description:
Substantial spaces, unlimited potential
An exceptional offering on a 692m2 allotment (approx.), this substantial five bedroom three bathroom home presents an opportunity of unsurpassed potential. With two self-contained units and ROW on two sides, this remarkable property, moments to Sydney Road, Coburg Station and schools, sits at the heart of a lifestyle locale. Offering lavish accommodation this expansive home resplendent with leadlight details, decorative ceilings and ornate timber trims, features formal living and dining, sunlit informal domain boasting a timber kitchen with 900mm Emilia range, and spacious rear incorporating one and two bedroom self-contained bungalows, ideal for extended families or a potential rental opportunity. Including heating/cooling, attic storage, exceptional OSP, carport plus workshop, it offers exciting scope for further renovation or outstanding redevelopment (STCA).
Insights: 57 Linsey Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 12 other 5 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Merri Creek Outlook
Brilliantly positioned at the end of a no-through street with views across Merri Creek, this well presented home boasts lots of character and a massive 710 square metre allotment with two separate bungalows in the big backyard. A large front patio overlooking Merri Creek introduces the main house with an inviting air through the lounge/dining warmed by polished timber floors and a cosy open fire. Double doors open to the elevated front deck taking in those idyllic views. The updated kitchen with breakfast bar adjoins the good-size meals area with French doors leading to the entertaining and three robed bedrooms area serviced by the spa bathroom and second toilet off the laundry. The two bungalows at the rear consist of a bed-sitter with bathroom and studio with loft, easily earning you quality rental returns. There's plenty of space out front for off street parking which also includes an electric vehicle charger. Shops, schools and transport are all within easy reach.
Insights: 1 Booth Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Zone in on quality contemporary living
Tucked away in a quiet yet convenient position, south of Bell Street and zoned to Strathmore College, this three bedroom plus study, two bathroom contemporary residence shines with reverse living design. Sunny and spacious, the kitchen/dining/living is linked by slide apart glass doors to a balcony. A waterfall stone counter and stainless steel appliances are in place and there's also a courtyard to enjoy below. Double bedrooms host mirrored built-in robes, the fitted study with exceptionally long desk is a real bonus, while the main bathroom flaunts a deep bath and there's a sleek ensuite and powder room. Heating, cooling, video intercom, an alarm, laundry, storage and direct entry double garage, to rear right of way, also star. Stroll to schools, trams, buses, Bush Reserve and shops.
Insights: 2/90 Bruce Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Style Meets Character In Fantastic Locale
Beautiful presentation and innovative design has transformed this two bedroom Californian Bungalow into something truly special.
Timber floors line a spacious living and study domain, leading through the hall way which offers two bedrooms with central bathroom, the master featuring a split system heating/cooling and BIRs, along with a foldable staircase leading to roof storage space.
Featuring a well-equipped kitchen with granite benchtops, Smeg appliances including a 900mm oven and gas cooktop, and myrtle timber cupboards with ample storage space. This leads into the dining/family room and undercover decking area, perfect for indoor/outdoor entertaining. There is also off street parking for two cars along with a full side drive leading to a garage/shed area, spilt system heating/cooling in both living areas, an open fireplace, solar panels and well-manicured gardens.
All within close proximity to Coburg North shopping precinct, Batman & Coburg Railway Stations, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market and the Merri Creek bike trail.
Insights: 3 A'beckett Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.
